text: Daniela Regula Schwarz (born 9 September 1985) is a Swiss football defender, playing for Norwegian Toppserien club Vålerenga. She previously played for Grasshopper Club Zürich of the Nationalliga A. Since her debut in July 2009, a 5–0 defeat by the Netherlands, she has been a member of the Switzerland women's national football team.Portrait in the Swiss Football Association's page A product of the America college soccer system, Schwarz attended Lindsey Wilson and also played in the North American W-League for F.C. Indiana and Toronto Lady Lynx.
